1. Hyperlinks are clickable text labels that navigate to new content.
1. On hover, links are depicted with a solid underline to indicate the expected
behavior is navigational and will not perform an action that affects data.
1. When clicked, a Hyperlink takes the user to a new web page,
or to a different part of the same page (e.g., an anchor).
